# Supabase Edge Functions

- **Business logic belongs here**—not in the React app. Put domain rules, workflow branching, LawHub calls, and authoritative validation in **`*.service.ts`** (orchestration) and **`*.repository.ts`** (persistence). The frontend should only invoke functions and render results.
- One **feature folder** per function (e.g. `supabase/functions/users/`).
- **Layers** (same basename prefix):
  - `*.controller.ts` — HTTP: method/body, status codes, CORS.
  - `*.service.ts` — Orchestration; call LawHub when needed; no raw SQL.
  - `*.repository.ts` — Supabase **service role** DB access only.
  - `*.mapper.ts` — Pure mapping LawHub/LSAC JSON ↔ app types (unit-test heavily).
- **`index.ts`** — Thin entry: `Deno.serve` → controller only.
- **Shared** HTTP/token helpers → `supabase/functions/_shared/` (inject `fetch` for tests).
- **Secrets**: LSAC + service role keys via **Supabase secrets** / local env—never commit.
